message.content: The EntleBucher is a breed of dog that originates from Switzerland. It is a medium-sized dog with a muscular and compact build, with a height ranging from 16 to 21 inches and weighing between 45 to 65 pounds. The coat of an EntleBucher is dense, shiny, and short, with a tricolour combination of black, white, and rust colours. It has a broad and flat skull with a strong jaw and square muzzle. The nose is black and the ears are small, triangular, and set high on the head. The EntleBucher is a working dog and is used as a herding and cattle driving dog in its native Switzerland. It is also used for search and rescue missions and as a watchdog. Overall, the EntleBucher is a sturdy and agile dog with a loyal and protective temperament.
